  "articleSummary": "This tutorial introduces JavaScript Promises as a reliable mechanism for managing asynchronous operations that may either succeed or fail. It outlines how to instantiate promises using `Promise.resolve()` or the `Promise` constructor, and demonstrates handling outcomes through the `.then()` and `.catch()` instance methods alongside utility functions like `Promise.all()` and `Promise.race()`. Written in a clear, instructional tone, the article targets beginner to intermediate JavaScript developers and uses a resolve/reject flowchart to visually frame the promise lifecycle.",
